Class Maximum

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.BaseCount<Maximum>
com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.Maximum
All Implemented Interfaces:
Countable, NextIterator<Maximum>, Mapper<Long,Maximum>, Arithmetic<Maximum>, Maximizable<Maximum>, Minimizable<Maximum>, Numeric<Maximum>, Zeroable, AsString, StringFormattable, DoubleValued, FormattedLongValued, LongValued, Source<Long>, Comparable<Countable>, Supplier<Long>
public class Maximum extends BaseCount<Maximum>
A count value that is an maximum. This class mainly exists to clarify APIs by giving a meaning to the count value.
